item.dc:creator: @Your_Grandpa Your Grandpa
item.description:
@Your_Grandpa wrote:

[quote=“Bang Train, post:24, topic:10764”][quote author=Your Grandpa link=topic=15810.msg191832#msg191832 date=1156775149]

i like java (im learning) but i suck at grammer when i type so i always put system instead of System and shit

also PHP is not programming language since theres no compiling. a scripting language seems more accurate

to me atleast

p.s. i like PHP’

AND SQL IS NOT A DAMN LANGAUGE GOD DAMN

INSERT INTO ‘table’ Values (‘sex’,‘me’,‘now’)

IS NOT PROGRAMMING GOD DAMN…

http://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.0/en/create-procedure.html
[/quote]

who the hell would waste their time with that when u can do it with php and make more sense :-D[/quote]
Possible cases:

[ul][]The amount of data needed to process is much larger than the data you need to output, why transfer the bulk when you can transfer just the end result?
[]You need to use the same functions in different languages, instead of a function for C++, Java & PHP, you write one in SQL.[/ul]

I’m sure there are more, but these are just the basic ones. You can do all graphic processing in the processor, yet all gaming machines use separate video cards for that
